critique: This document is an executive order from Franklin D. Roosevelt approving a code of fair competition for the newsprint industry under the National Industrial Recovery Act of 1933. It reflects a strong interventionist approach to economic regulation, typical of the New Deal era. The order also touches on labor standards by setting a minimum wage condition. There is no direct impact on immigration, executive power, federalism, national security, or social inclusion. Therefore, the primary focus is on economic regulation.
